---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Research Methodology"
  description="How Cape Town Invest researches South African property data — sources, limitations, and partner referral policy."
>
  <section class="site-container py-12 md:py-16 max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="mb-6">Methodology</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Our guides combine publicly available South African sources (Lightstone, Deeds Office commentary, SARS guidance,
        City of Cape Town bylaws), independent market research, and cross-checks against multiple listing platforms.
        Figures are rounded and dated — Western Cape prices and visa thresholds move quickly.
      </p>
      <h2>Sources we prioritise</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Registered transaction data and published house-price indices (Lightstone, FNB, John Loos research)</li>
        <li>Official Home Affairs and SARS guidance for visa and tax thresholds (always verified at application time)</li>
        <li>Licensed conveyancer and property practitioner commentary (clearly labelled as third-party)</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Lead referral policy</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit the shortlist or consultation form, your enquiry may be shared with a
        <strong>licensed South African property partner</strong> who can show regulated inventory and complete FICA.
        We do not sell your data to unrelated marketing lists.
      </p>
      <h2>Yield and investment disclaimers</h2>
      <p>
        Rental yields cited on this site are typically <em>modeled</em> from indicative rents and costs unless stated otherwise.
        They are not guarantees. Always rebuild net yield with current levies, rates, vacancy, and management fees.
      </p>
      <h2>Updates</h2>
      <p>
        Each guide shows an <em>Updated</em> date when material facts change (transfer duty bands, visa income floors, major market shifts).
        Always confirm numbers with your conveyancer, tax adviser, and immigration practitioner before signing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
